<<.from-version "5.5.0">>

The <<.op checkbox>> operator works in two modes depending on the optional suffix.

!! Title-returning mode (no suffix)

Returns tiddler titles from the input that contain wikitext checkbox syntax (`[ ]`, `[x]`, or `[X]`).

|!Operand |!Meaning |
|''(empty)'' |at least one checkbox of any state |
|`checked` |at least one checked checkbox (`[x]` or `[X]`) |
|`unchecked` |at least one unchecked checkbox (`[ ]`) |

The negated form (`[!checkbox[...]]`) returns titles with //no// matching checkboxes.

!! Text-extracting mode (`:text` suffix)

`[checkbox:text[checked]]` — instead of returning tiddler titles, returns the text content of each matching checkbox item (everything after the `[ ]`/`[x]`/`[X]` marker on the same line), one result per checkbox item across all input tiddlers.

|!Usage |!Returns |
|`[checkbox:text[]]` |text of every checkbox item (any state) |
|`[checkbox:text[checked]]` |text of every checked checkbox item |
|`[checkbox:text[unchecked]]` |text of every unchecked checkbox item |

''Note:'' Both modes scan the raw wikitext and will also match checkboxes inside code blocks or comments.

! Examples

```
[all[tiddlers]checkbox[]]
```
Returns all tiddlers that contain any checkbox.

```
[all[tiddlers]checkbox[unchecked]]
```
Returns all tiddlers that have at least one unchecked task.

```
[all[tiddlers]!checkbox[]]
```
Returns all tiddlers that have no checkboxes at all.

```
[all[tiddlers]checkbox:text[unchecked]]
```
Returns the text of every unchecked task item across all tiddlers.

